{
  "text": "Thirty consecutive patients with PCa who were considered as high risk for metastases (PSA > 20 ng/ml, Gleason \u2265 8, or T stage \u2265 3a) [CITATION_1] were prospectively enrolled between February and December 2012. The mean patient age (\u00b1stand-ard deviation) was 69 \u00b1 3.3 years. The mean prostate-specific antigen level was 31 \u00b1 28 ng/mL. Three patients were not enrolled because of contraindications to MR imaging.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "52862557"
